The strategy in this proof is essentially the same as explored in . To prove independence, we must prove that the assumption
\begin{split} k \uvec{v} + \amp a_1 \uvec{v}_1 + a_2 \uvec{v}_2 + \dotsb + a_\ell \uvec{v}_\ell \\ \amp + b_1 \uvec{w}_1 + b_2 \uvec{w}_2 + \dotsb + b_m \uvec{w}_m = \zerovec \end{split}
leads to the conclusion that each of the scalars k,a_1,a_2,\dotsc,a_\ell,b_1,b_2,\dotsc,b_m is 0.
